WEBVTT

00:03.833 --> 00:06.301
Why do I have to move?
This is a city street!

00:06.303 --> 00:08.229
Because you're obstructing
pedestrian traffic.

00:08.230 --> 00:09.642
Now, if you don't move
across the street,

00:09.643 --> 00:11.577
I'm gonna have to write you up
for disorderly conduct.

00:11.578 --> 00:14.579
Oh, I <i>am</i> disorderly,
and I'm gonna be disorderly

00:14.581 --> 00:16.648
until my son's killer is found.

00:16.650 --> 00:18.183
Go ahead and
look at me!

00:18.185 --> 00:20.252
I'm a mother whose
son was killed,

00:20.254 --> 00:22.187
and these cops around
here don't give

00:22.189 --> 00:24.189
a good damn!
You. Hey.

00:24.191 --> 00:25.957
Look at me.
Are you a detective?

00:25.959 --> 00:27.259
Yeah, I'm a detective. Why?

00:27.261 --> 00:30.195
Well, I want you and all your
detective friends to know

00:30.197 --> 00:32.296
that I'm gonna stand
out here every day

00:32.299 --> 00:33.598
until someone
listens to me

00:33.600 --> 00:35.167
and finds out who
killed my boy,

00:35.169 --> 00:36.635
because I deserve
to know who...

00:36.637 --> 00:38.470
Okay. What's your
boy's name, ma'am?

00:38.472 --> 00:41.440
Amir Christopher Brown, and
it's been a hundred and for...

00:41.442 --> 00:43.442
146 days. I can see
the sign, ma'am,

00:43.444 --> 00:46.478
and I can hear you screaming--
I'll take a look at it.

00:46.480 --> 00:47.202
You'll "take a look"?

00:47.226 --> 00:48.881
What does that even mean,
you'll "take a look"?

00:48.882 --> 00:51.049
It means I'll take a look at it.

00:51.051 --> 00:53.952
It better mean you are going
to get justice for Amir,

00:53.954 --> 00:56.354
because tomorrow
is 147 days,

00:56.356 --> 00:59.091
and I will still be out
here demanding justice

00:59.093 --> 01:01.760
for my son!

01:01.762 --> 01:02.761
You gonna hit me?

01:02.763 --> 01:03.962
I didn't call
no cops!

01:03.964 --> 01:07.099
(all shouting)

01:07.101 --> 01:08.233
Central, 12-David, 10-84.

01:08.235 --> 01:10.335
Hey. Hey. Back up.
Hey! Back it up!

01:10.337 --> 01:11.636
(indistinct shouting)

01:11.638 --> 01:12.971
- Hey, calm down. Hey, calm down.
- Hey, hey.

01:12.973 --> 01:15.006
- What... Will you tell me what happened?
- He's a psycho!

01:15.008 --> 01:16.174
Calm down! Look, calm down!

01:16.176 --> 01:18.276
Get off me, man.
We got this.

01:18.278 --> 01:20.679
- Can you give us a hand with the crowd?
- Yeah, you got it. Eddie!

01:20.681 --> 01:22.280
Eddie, hey. All right,
everybody just back it up.

01:22.282 --> 01:23.448
Step back. Step back.
Step back.

01:23.450 --> 01:24.816
JANKO:
Please...

01:24.818 --> 01:26.084
(woman screams)

01:26.652 --> 01:28.019
Hey! You good?

01:28.021 --> 01:29.688
I'm good! Go, go.

01:30.389 --> 01:31.490
Hey! Police! Stop!

01:31.492 --> 01:32.390
Let's cut him off.

01:32.392 --> 01:35.193
♪ ♪

01:35.195 --> 01:36.194
Stop!

01:36.196 --> 01:37.395
Hold it right there!

01:37.397 --> 01:38.230
Police!

01:38.232 --> 01:40.732
Hey! Police!

01:45.538 --> 01:47.272
(Eddie shouts)

01:47.274 --> 01:49.040
DUNLEEVY:
Stop!

01:49.042 --> 01:50.475
Hey!

01:53.679 --> 01:55.147
(grunts)

01:57.150 --> 01:59.217
Eddie! Eddie!

02:00.486 --> 02:02.587
(gasping)

02:02.589 --> 02:05.757
You hit? Where you hit?
Where you hit?

02:05.759 --> 02:07.325
Where you hit?

02:11.564 --> 02:13.098
Didn't go through.
It didn't go through.

02:13.100 --> 02:14.332
It didn't go through.
You're all right.

02:14.334 --> 02:15.100
You're okay. Hang tight.

02:15.102 --> 02:16.735
MILLER:
He's hit!

02:19.238 --> 02:21.206
JAMIE:
Call a bus. Call a bus!

02:21.208 --> 02:24.309
Hey! Hey, Dunleevy, hey.
10-13.

02:24.311 --> 02:25.510
10-13, officer down.
Gunshots fired.

02:25.512 --> 02:26.912
Officer down!

02:26.914 --> 02:28.180
Hey, you all right?

02:28.182 --> 02:30.182
Hey, talk to me.
Dunleevy, stay with me.

02:30.184 --> 02:31.583
Hey, Andrew.
Hey, talk to me.

02:31.585 --> 02:33.785
Hey. Stay with me,
all right, bud?

02:33.787 --> 02:35.187
I remember this case.

02:35.189 --> 02:37.255
Amir Brown--
he was shot outside a nightclub

02:37.257 --> 02:38.824
in the, uh, Village, right?

02:38.826 --> 02:41.993
Yeah, at 3:00 a.m. on October 3
outside Bar Sixteen.

02:41.995 --> 02:44.729
Two shots to the chest
with a .45-caliber.

02:44.731 --> 02:47.699
What the hell are you doing?
You snooping around my case?

02:47.701 --> 02:49.968
Well, I didn't know
it was your case anymore.

02:49.970 --> 02:53.004
What are you talking about?
It's been open for 146 days,

02:53.006 --> 02:54.339
you haven't cracked it,

02:54.341 --> 02:56.241
and we got a mom who's
wondering who killed her son.

02:56.243 --> 02:58.610
Ah, she got to you, too, huh?
Let me tell you something,

02:58.612 --> 02:59.606
her son was a dirtbag.

02:59.630 --> 03:02.229
I didn't know we only
closed cases on vics we like.

03:02.282 --> 03:04.883
Son of a bitch. Why don't I take some
of your cases, would you like that?

03:04.885 --> 03:07.853
You couldn't, because I,
unlike you, close my cases.

03:07.855 --> 03:09.487
- Hey.
- Hey!

03:09.489 --> 03:10.956
You got a real problem, man.

03:10.958 --> 03:13.358
(shouting)
Break it up.

03:13.360 --> 03:14.492
Get your hands off me.

03:14.494 --> 03:15.560
You're a jag-off!

03:15.562 --> 03:17.329
Get off me!

03:19.031 --> 03:21.066
This is our squad!

03:22.335 --> 03:23.802
My case.

03:23.804 --> 03:28.039
GARRETT: Officer Andrew John Dunleevy
was shot and killed

03:28.041 --> 03:31.042
at approximately 9:45 a.m. today

03:31.044 --> 03:33.945
without provocation
and while performing his duties

03:33.947 --> 03:36.815
as a New York City
police officer.

03:36.817 --> 03:38.149
He was...

03:38.151 --> 03:41.353
on the job for five years
and was...

03:41.355 --> 03:44.122
an exemplary police officer.

03:44.124 --> 03:47.092
Our hearts and prayers and
gratitude for his service

03:47.094 --> 03:50.095
go out to his widow
Stephanie and his...

03:50.097 --> 03:51.830
children, Jason and Anne.

03:51.832 --> 03:55.166
Officer Edit Janko
was also hit with gunfire.

03:55.168 --> 03:57.435
Her bulletproof vest
saved her life.

03:57.437 --> 04:00.105
She is recovering
from blunt force trauma

04:00.107 --> 04:01.573
in the E.R.

04:01.575 --> 04:02.941
The shooter...

04:02.943 --> 04:06.511
Malcolm James, 21,
of East New York,

04:06.513 --> 04:09.447
is in custody
at this time.

04:09.449 --> 04:10.916
We'll take questions.

04:10.918 --> 04:12.317
Helen.

04:12.319 --> 04:15.220
Commissioner, what do we know
about the reason for the attack?

04:15.222 --> 04:18.723
Officers Dunleevy, Miller,
Reagan and Janko responded

04:18.725 --> 04:22.594
to a 911 call
about a domestic disturbance.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.896
Malcolm James, by all accounts,

04:24.898 --> 04:28.333
fired first and without warning.

04:28.335 --> 04:29.401
Robert.

04:29.403 --> 04:31.069
Has Malcolm James
made a statement?

04:31.071 --> 04:33.571
- Well...
- At this time, we know that

04:33.573 --> 04:37.042
the police responded
to a 911 call,

04:37.044 --> 04:39.978
which resulted
in this young man being pursued

04:39.980 --> 04:41.680
by our officers.

04:41.682 --> 04:43.548
And in answer to
your question,

04:43.550 --> 04:45.350
the investigation
is ongoing.

04:45.352 --> 04:46.851
Madame Mayor,
you're saying

04:46.853 --> 04:49.788
police were chasing the subject
at the time of the shooting?

04:49.790 --> 04:51.156
The suspect was running
from the cops?

04:51.158 --> 04:53.959
Perhaps he felt threatened.
We don't know.

04:53.961 --> 04:56.294
And as soon as we
ascertain the details...

04:56.296 --> 04:58.997
Then we will issue
a joint press release.

04:58.999 --> 05:00.231
But, Madame Mayor,
are you saying that

05:00.233 --> 05:01.666
Malcolm James fired because

05:01.668 --> 05:02.867
he was scared for his life?

05:02.869 --> 05:06.404
Listen, anyone,
especially a minority,

05:06.406 --> 05:08.306
being chased by police

05:08.308 --> 05:10.608
would be afraid for their life.

05:10.610 --> 05:12.577
So did he shoot at cops...
(reporters clamoring)

05:12.579 --> 05:15.080
GARRETT:
Hey, let's bring it back.

05:15.082 --> 05:16.381
(clamoring continues)

